# Import dataset that contains country data
mapdata <- read.csv("paper_info.csv", na.strings = "")

# Create an object that counts the number of publications in each country
map_count <- count(mapdata, vars = Country)

# Select the middle 7 colours from the 13 of the plasma clour palette from
# the viridis package in reverse order
mypal <- plasma(13, alpha = 0.8)[10:4]

# join map_count data to a coarse resolution map
spdf <- joinCountryData2Map(map_count, joinCode = "NAME", nameJoinColumn = "vars")
## 10 codes from your data successfully matched countries in the map
## 0 codes from your data failed to match with a country code in the map
## 233 codes from the map weren't represented in your data
# png('map.png', width = 15, height = 10, units = 'cm', res = 300)

# Create country plot
mapParams <- mapCountryData(spdf, nameColumnToPlot = "n", catMethod = "fixedwidth", 
    addLegend = FALSE, colourPalette = mypal, mapTitle = "", oceanCol = "gray97", 
    missingCountryCol = "white", borderCol = "grey40")

# Add legend
do.call(addMapLegend, c(mapParams, legendLabels = "all", horizontal = TRUE, 
    legendWidth = 0.5, legendIntervals = "data", legendMar = 5))

Proportion of effect sizes by face sample and paper

# Function to calculate the angle at which to rotate the label in a pie
# chart. For readability.
compute_angle = function(perc) {
    ifelse(perc < 0.25, 90 - ((perc/0.25) * 90), ifelse(perc >= 0.25 & perc < 
        0.5, (perc - 0.25)/0.25 * -90, ifelse(perc >= 0.5 & perc < 0.75, 90 - 
        ((perc - 0.5)/0.25 * 90), ifelse(perc >= 0.75 & perc < 1, ((perc - 0.75)/0.25) * 
        -90, 0))))
}

# Create the paper level dataframe first
faceset_data_freq <- select(data, c(Paper, FaceSample)) %>% count(FaceSample, 
    Paper) %>% group_by(FaceSample) %>% mutate(nSamplvl = sum(n)) %>% arrange(-nSamplvl, 
    -n) %>% select(-nSamplvl) %>% ungroup() %>% mutate(proportion = n/sum(n)) %>% 
    mutate(ymax = cumsum(proportion)) %>% mutate(ymin = ifelse(ymax != 0, lag(ymax), 
    "0")) %>% mutate(running = cumsum(n), pos = running - n/2, perc = pos/sum(n)) %>% 
    mutate(angle = compute_angle(perc)) %>% mutate(percent = n/sum(n) * 100)
faceset_data_freq$ymin[is.na(faceset_data_freq$ymin)] <- 0

# Create the face sample dataframe
sample_data <- select(faceset_data_freq, c(FaceSample, n, ymax, ymin)) %>% group_by(FaceSample) %>% 
    summarise(n = sum(n), ymax = max(ymax), ymin = min(ymin)) %>% arrange(-n) %>% 
    ungroup() %>% mutate(running = cumsum(n), pos = running - n/2, perc = pos/sum(n)) %>% 
    mutate(angle = compute_angle(perc))

# Create multilevel pie chart (aka Piedonut chart) using ggplot by creating
# a barplot with the paper level data for one bar and the face sample level
# data for the other bar and then bend the bars into a circle.
ggplot() + geom_bar(aes(x = 1, y = 71), fill = "white", stat = "identity", width = 0.2) + 
    geom_bar(data = sample_data, aes(fill = n, y = n, x = 2), color = "black", 
        position = "stack", stat = "identity", size = 0.1, width = 1.5, alpha = 0.7) + 
    geom_text(data = sample_data, aes(label = paste(FaceSample), x = 2.3, y = pos, 
        angle = angle)) + geom_bar(data = faceset_data_freq, aes(fill = n, y = n, 
    x = 3.6), color = "black", position = "stack", stat = "identity", size = 0.1, 
    width = 1.5, alpha = 0.7) + geom_text(data = faceset_data_freq, aes(label = paste0(Paper, 
    " ", "(", round(percent, digits = 2), "%)"), x = 3.6, y = pos, angle = angle)) + 
    scale_fill_distiller(palette = "BuPu", direction = 1) + coord_polar(theta = "y") + 
    theme_void() + theme(legend.position = "none") + theme(legend.title = element_blank())

# ggsave('piedonut_BuPu2.pdf', width = 25, height = 25, units=c('cm') )

Proportion of effect sizes by ethnicity of faces and raters

# Create a separate dataframe for the ethnicity data
ethnicity_data_freq <- select(data, c(Ethnicity_face, Ethnicity_rater)) %>% 
    count(Ethnicity_face, Ethnicity_rater, sort = TRUE)

# Alluvial plot linking the effect sizes by ethnicity. Ethnicity of faces on
# the left and perceivers on the right
ggplot(ethnicity_data_freq, aes(y = n, axis1 = Ethnicity_face, axis2 = Ethnicity_rater)) + 
    geom_alluvium(aes(fill = Ethnicity_face), width = 1/12, knot.pos = 0.4) + 
    geom_stratum(width = 1/6, color = "grey") + geom_text(stat = "stratum", 
    aes(label = after_stat(stratum))) + scale_x_discrete(limits = c("Faces", 
    "Perceivers"), expand = c(0.05, 0.05)) + scale_fill_manual(values = c("#2626BB", 
    "#7C7CE5", "#4747DA", "#B1B1EF")) + ylab("No. of effect sizes") + theme_minimal() + 
    theme(legend.position = "none", axis.title.y = element_text(size = 18, face = "bold"), 
        axis.text.y = element_text(size = 18), axis.text.x = element_text(size = 18, 
            face = "bold"))

Co-author network figure

# Import .bib file of the included papers
bib <- convert2df("savedrecs.bib", dbsource = "isi", format = "bibtex")
## 
## Converting your isi collection into a bibliographic dataframe
## 
## Done!
## 
## 
## Generating affiliation field tag AU_UN from C1:  Done!
test <- bib$AU
test2 <- unlist(strsplit(test, ";"))
test2 <- test2[order(test2)]

# see which names need cleaning
View(test2)
View(test)

# write.csv(test2, 'author_list_uncleaned.csv', row.names = FALSE)

# Do some cleaning (fix author initials)
test3 <- paste(test, ";", sep = "")
corrected <- gsub("LITTLE DI;", "LITTLE AC;", test3, ignore.case = TRUE)
bib$AU <- corrected  #add corrections

# Create co-author network plot png('Figure_collaboration_network.png',
# width = 10, height = 10, units = 'cm', res = 300)
par(mfrow = c(1, 1), mar = c(0, 0, 0, 0))
M <- metaTagExtraction(bib, Field = "CR_AU", sep = ";")
NetMatrix <- biblioNetwork(M, analysis = "collaboration", network = "authors", 
    sep = ";")
net <- networkPlot(NetMatrix, n = 1e+10, cluster = "walktrap", Title = "", labelsize = 0.7, 
    type = "fruchterman", size = TRUE, remove.multiple = TRUE)
